The paper deals with the traveling salesman problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and optimization. The paper presents an algorithm that computes a polynomial time approximation to the optimal tour in TSP instances that form an arbitrary metric space with bounded intrinsic dimension. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with algorithmic and geometric aspects of TSP. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves some theoretical and numerical analysis.
